Comment 1: Linden: Vehicles routinely speed over the crest at the intersection of Devenish & Pinedale St. There are several driveway crossovers and exiting is very hazardous. There are also a number of schools nearby and the neighbourhood is populated by young families. Current traffic calming measures are ineffective and the council refuses to take action. We have CCTV footage of negligent / malicious speeding along this road and it's only a matter of time before there is a major accident.
Comment 2: Gary: Vehicles travcelling over the blind crest on Devenish St, at the corner of Langler and Pinedale Streets, at speeds over 100kph. I have video footage of this happening. Near misses where speeding vehicles have narrlowly avoided colliding with traffic entering from side streets. Road rage between drivers and drivers v pedestrians. Cars taking the corner of Pinedale and Devenish St too quickly and mounting the footpath. Drivers having no regard for current traffic calming measures.
